description:
Define and implement the configuration schema for remote-skills:

```jsonc
{
  "remote-skills": {
    "repositories": [
      {
        "url": "git@github.com:company/shared-skills.git",
        "ref": "main",  // branch, tag, or commit SHA (optional)
        "skills": ["code-review", "kotlin-pro"]  // optional, imports all if omitted
      }
    ],
    "sync": "blocking" | "background"  // default: blocking
  }
}
```

- Use Zod for schema validation
- Support reading from opencode.json config
- Provide TypeScript types for the config

Update `src/index.ts` to collect instructions from sync results and inject them into config.

## Implementation Details

### Update performSync() Return Type
Add remoteInstructions to the return:
```typescript
async function performSync(config: RemoteSkillsConfig): Promise<{
  results: SyncResult[]
  skippedConflicts: string[]
  totalSkills: number
  remoteAgents: Map<string, RemoteAgent>
  remoteCommands: Map<string, RemoteCommand>
  remoteInstructions: string[]  // NEW - absolute paths
  pluginsChanged: boolean
  totalPlugins: number
}>
```

### Collect Instructions in performSync()
```typescript
// Collect instructions from all repositories (no first-wins, append all)
const remoteInstructions: string[] = []
for (const result of results) {
  if (result.error) continue
  for (const instruction of result.instructions) {
    remoteInstructions.push(instruction.path)
  }
}

if (remoteInstructions.length > 0) {
  log(`Discovered ${remoteInstructions.length} remote instructions`)
}
```

### Update Config Hook
```typescript
config: async (config) => {
  // ... existing agent/command injection ...

  // Inject instructions
  if (remoteInstructions.length > 0) {
    // Ensure config.instructions is an array
    if (!Array.isArray(config.instructions)) {
      config.instructions = config.instructions ? [config.instructions] : []
    }

    // Append all remote instructions
    config.instructions.push(...remoteInstructions)
    log(`Appended ${remoteInstructions.length} remote instructions`)
  }
}
```

### Update Summary Log
Include instructions count in the summary message:
```typescript
if (remoteInstructions.length > 0) parts.push(`${remoteInstructions.length} instructions`)
```

## Dependencies
- Depends on: git.ts updates (Task 3)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] performSync collects instruction paths from all repos
- [ ] Config hook appends instructions to config.instructions
- [ ] Handles missing/undefined config.instructions gracefully
- [ ] Logs instruction counts
- [ ] Summary message includes instruction count

